Title: Creating a co_await awaitable signal that can be awaited multiple times, part 2 | The Old New Thing
Description: Last time, we created an awaitable signal that can be awaited multiple times. We noted that one problem with the implementation is that the object couldn’t be copied: Everybody has to await the same object, which can create lifetime issues. One way of solving this is to put the awaitable_event inside a shared_ptr and having everybody share the lifetime.
